<h3>Why "Memecoop"?</h3>

<p>
Much of the philosophy and design of this project is derived from a recently blossoming branch of
science called <%= link_to "memetics", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memetics" %>, the study of the
evolution of ideas. A "meme" is the basic unit of memetics: that which is copied from brain to
brain. Since we're building a platform for memes to be bred more efficiently, we liked the metaphor
of thinking of them as eggs being incubated in a chicken coop. Technically, it's also short for the
Memetics Cooperative, but we prefer to keep things informal :)
</p>
